# docs/

Technical documentation for Intent v2.9.0, covering the rule library, Critic subagents, extension authoring, and audit processes. These guides are the canonical reference for Intent developers and extension authors.

## Dirs

- `blog/` -- Published blog posts and articles on Intent concepts and workflows
- `releases/` -- Release notes and changelog summaries by version (2.5.0+)

## Files

- `rules.md` -- Intent rules authoring guide; covers rule ID scheme, detection heuristics, and library layout
- `critics.md` -- Critic subagent contract and invocation signatures; enforcement, report format, and rule loading order
- `writing-extensions.md` -- User extension authoring guide; manifest schema, discovery precedence, and validation
- `creating-custom-agents.md` -- Creating Intent agents (canon vs extension); agent structure and step-by-step process
- `total-codebase-audit.md` -- TCA v4.0 process guide; 5-phase audit pipeline and provisioning invariants for total codebase scans
